While many people are happy using <<.graph>>'s [[GUI]] to create common graphs, using all of its built-in templates and widgets, but maybe you'd like to create your //own// templates and widgets, because you have a specific kind of graph in mind, with specific style and behavior.

For that, you can use the [[API]]. <<.graph>> defines a whole set of widgets which can act as building blocks to make exactly the kind of graph you have in mind, from exact style, to custom behavior.

This tutorial will cover the core concepts important to know when using the widgets. We'll start with a simple Hello World and build up from there with larger and larger building blocks.
